      <subsection name="6.0.0">
        <p class="smallinfo">Release Date: 23 Aug 2022</p>
        <ul>
          <li><a href='https://issues.onehippo.com/browse/HIPFORGE-421'>HIPFORGE-421</a> -
            Upgrade for XM 15 compatibility.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </subsection>
      <subsection name="5.0.0">
        <p class="smallinfo">Release Date: 12 May 2021</p>
        <ul>
          <li><a href='https://issues.onehippo.com/browse/HIPFORGE-405'>HIPFORGE-405</a> -
            Upgrade for XM 14 compatibility.<br/>
          </li>
          <li>The artifacts' groupId was changed from <code>org.onehippo.forge.doc-commenting</code> to
            <code>org.<b>bloomreach</b>.forge.doc-commenting</code> (but no repackaging of Java classes though).</li>
          <li>Added bootstrapping of domain <code>/hippo:configuration/hippo:domains/doccommenting</code> to the plugin, instead of
            doing this in an implementing project. Please check the upgrade path: best approach
            is to first remove this node from project yamls, then redo any changes.</li>
        </ul>
      </subsection>
      <subsection name="4.0.0">
        <p class="smallinfo">Release Date: 19 January 2019</p>
        <ul>
          <li><a href='https://issues.onehippo.com/browse/HIPFORGE-251'>HIPFORGE-251</a> -
            Upgrade for XM 13 compatibility.</li>
